    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Hendrickson suspension systems use equalizing ("walking") beams to distribute the vehicle load between
                tandem axles, and to reduce the effect of road bumps. The pivot points (centers) of the two beams are
                connected by a cross tube that passes through the inner metals of the beam center bushings. The cross
                tube aligns the suspensions system correctly, and prevents load transfer damage by restricting lateral
                (side-to-side) axle movement during turning (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300601">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300601" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300601" filename="../figg03/G0300601.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Hendrickson Suspension System</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.TORQUE ROD CROSSMEMBER BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.END BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.BEAM END CONNECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.CROSS TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.CENTER BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>7.EQUALIZING BEAM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Bushings in the beam centers and ends, and in the torque rods, permit the articulation of the axles
                without friction or metal-to-metal contact (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300602">Figure 2</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300603">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300602" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300602" filename="../figg03/G0300602.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Bushings - Hendrickson Suspension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.MOUNTING BRACKET (WELDED ONTO AXLE)</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.BAR PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.BOLT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.BEAM END</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.NUT/WASHER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300603" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300603" filename="../figg03/G0300603.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Bushings - Hendrickson Suspension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1.MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2.BAR PIN WITH SHIMS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3.BOLT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4.BEAM END</callout1>
                    <callout1>5.NUT/WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6.ADJUSTER SHIMS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Torque rods mount on the top of each axle and attach to the frame crossmember to absorb acceleration
                and braking inertia of the axles.
            </para>
            <para>For tandem axles, Hendrickson permits flexibility between the axles, withstands rugged usage with long
                service life, and exhibits true running characteristics. These suspension systems are used for
                on-and-off highway applications.
            </para>
            <para>These are the two types of Hendrickson suspension systems used by International:</para>
            <para>Leaf spring type (U/UE, RT/RTE AND RT2/RTE2 Series)</para>
            <para>Load cushion type (RS Series)</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>As of October 1992, both Leaf spring and Load cushion type suspensions will have the BAR PIN
                        BEAM END DESIGN (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300602">Figure 2</hotlnk>and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300603">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300603">Figure 3</hotlnk>with the shim kit is for service only and not for
                        production.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
